The paper deals with the design and analysis of a coding scheme using lattice vector quantization for multiple description coding. This involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT) such as entropy-constrained coding, as well as multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI) due to the use of reconstruction functions. The paper also involves the use of nested lattices, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed scheme in terms of rate loss, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
